Steps to set up Docker volumes

- docker volume create pg-data
  docker volume create redis-server

Learnings about how Docker volumes work
1] Docker volumes are presistant data storage for docker containers, even the container stop or newly created volume data remains same.
2] to cretae docker volume , " docker volume create <volume_name> " command used.
3] to inspect the docker volume " docker volume inspect <volume_name> " command used.
4] to remove docker volume " docker volume rm <volume_name> " command used.
5] docker volume cant be attached to currently running conatainer directly.
